
Function and it's syntax


step 1 :- Function call 

        Syntax :- Function_Name(parameters if any ?  values or variables without data type);

        Example 1: - addition (a,b);            ----------> variables 
        Example 2: - addition (5,6);            ----------> values

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Step 2 : - Funcation Defination 

        Syntax :- "Return type" Function_Name (parameters if any ?  values or variables with data type)
                   {
                     Code 1;
                     Code 1;
                     Return statement if any   ?
                   }

        Example 1: - Void addition (int a,int b) ----------> Void Return type means no return. Variables with data type 
        Example 2: - int addition (int a,int b)
                        {  ----------> int Return type means return integer value. Variables with data type

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ 

Step 2 : - Funcation Declearation 

        Syntax :- "Return type" Function_Name (parameters if any ?  only data type without variables);

        Example 1: - Void addition (int ,int ); ----------> Void Return type means no return. Variables with data type 
        Example 2: - int addition (int ,int );  ----------> int Return type means return integer value. Variables with data type

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ 
Following types of Functions
 
1) Functions without parameter and without Return type  --------------> ()  & Void
2) Functions with parameter and without Return type    -------------->  (a,b)  & Void
3) Functions without parameter and with Return type    --------------> ()  & Int or float
4) Functions with parameter and with Return type       --------------> (a,b)  & int or float
